  <title>Format of 
	 <synph>href</synph> attribute in cross-references</title> 
  <shortdesc>The 
	 <synph>href</synph> attribute requires the address of the referenced
	 resource to be in the standard URI format. 
  </shortdesc> 
  <prolog><author>Tony
		Self</author><metadata><keywords><indexterm>URL</indexterm><indexterm>URI</indexterm><indexterm>href
			 attribute</indexterm><indexterm>attributes<indexterm>href</indexterm></indexterm><indexterm>elements<indexterm>xref</indexterm><indexterm>source</indexterm><indexterm>link</indexterm><indexterm>glossref</indexterm><indexterm>lq</indexterm></indexterm><indexterm>SMB</indexterm><indexterm>protocol</indexterm><indexterm>linking
			 protocol</indexterm><indexterm>ampersand character</indexterm><indexterm>slash
			 character</indexterm><indexterm>exemplar<indexterm>context-agnostic</indexterm><indexterm>conref</indexterm></indexterm><indexterm>backslash
			 character</indexterm><indexterm>resources<indexterm>links</indexterm></indexterm></keywords></metadata>
  </prolog> 
  <conbody> 
	 <p>The resources being referenced in 
		<synph>xref</synph>, 
		<synph>link</synph>, 
		<synph>lq</synph>, 
		<synph>glossref</synph>, and 
		<synph>source</synph> elements are specified in the 
		<synph>href</synph> attribute. 
	 </p> 
