	 <section id="section_729B7E8636104B6FABE4A5E3E9181601"
	  audience="contributor"> 
		<title>Rationale</title> 
		<lq reftitle="Deborah Pickett, Yahoo! DITA Users Group"
			href="http://tech.groups.yahoo.com/group/dita-users/message/15374" scope="external" format="html">DITA does
		  not speak in terms of file paths. It knows only URLs. When you use a DITA
		  document it is mandatory that you use URLs. Hence, as David said, don't say
		  "c:\My Documents", say "file:/c:/My%20Documents". Don't say "\\server\share",
		  say "smb://server/share". 
		</lq> 
